.TH LINK\-DOTFILES 1 "2026-04-04" "machine-setup 2.0" "Machine Setup Manual"
.SH NAME
link\-dotfiles.sh \- create symlinks for dotfiles from profile configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B link\-dotfiles.sh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates symbolic links in \fB$HOME\fR for dotfiles defined in the active
profile configuration. Existing files are backed up with a timestamped
suffix before linking. Supports nested directory structures and respects
platform-specific dotfile mappings.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Profile to use for dotfile selection.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what symlinks would be created without making changes.
.TP
.B \-\-force
Overwrite existing files without creating backups.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (missing profile, permission denied, broken source path).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Link dotfiles for the minimal profile:
.B link\-dotfiles.sh \-\-profile minimal
.TP
Preview dotfile linking:
.B link\-dotfiles.sh \-\-profile full \-\-dry\-run
.TP
Force-overwrite existing files:
.B link\-dotfiles.sh \-\-profile full \-\-force
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR setup.sh (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Machine Setup contributors.
